<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-02-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-02-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="198" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">
                            <persName corresp="#p_HICKERSONJD1">Hickerson</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_MURPHYRD1">Murphy</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_KEYDMK1">Key</persName> files, lot 58 D 33, “Secretary
                            Generalship of <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>”</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the United Nations
                                Adviser, Bureau of European Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_ALLENWP1"><hi rend="italic">Allen</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-02-19">February 19,
                                1953</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <item>Subject:</item>
                            <item>Length of <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>; Secretary
                                Generalship</item>
                        </list>
                        <list type="participants">
                            <item>Participants:</item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CARLIERG1">Georges Carlier</persName>,
                                Counselor, Belgian Embassy</item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ALLENWP1">Ward Allen</persName>, <gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss></item>
                        </list>
                        <p>Ambassador <persName>Zaroubin</persName> volunteered the following
                            comments to <persName corresp="#p_SILVERCRUYSBRS1">Baron
                                Silvercruys</persName> this morning as firm predictions: <list>
                                <label>1)</label>
                                <item>The <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> session will last at
                                    least through Easter;</item>
                                <label>2)</label>
                                <item>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LIETH1">Trygve Lie</persName> will
                                    continue as Secretary-General through the expiration of his
                                    present term. This, according to <persName>Zaroubin</persName>,
                                    is <persName corresp="#p_LIETH1">Lie</persName>’s dearest wish.
                                        <persName>Zaroubin</persName> strongly denied reports that
                                    the <gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss> has indicated it would
                                    accept <persName corresp="#p_PEARSONLB1">Pearson</persName>,
                                    but, of course, refused to say whether or not they would veto
                                    him.</item>
                            </list></p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>